ecycleEvent → handleLifecycleTurnStart()\\n```\\n\\n**I/O Operations:**\\n\\n1. **Parse input from stdin:**\\n   - Reads JSON from stdin (session_id, transcript_path, prompt)\\n\\n2. **Capture pre-prompt state:**\\n   - `CapturePrePromptState(ag, sessionID, event.SessionRef)` (from `state.go`, lines 92-146):\\n     - `paths.AbsPath()` - Uses repo root\\n     - **CREATES** `.entire/tmp/` directory\\n     - Get untracked files:\\n       - `openRepository()` - Opens `.git/` directory\\n       - `worktree.Status()` - **READS** working tree and index (git status)\\n       - **WRITES** `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-<sessionid>.json`\\n     - If agent has `TranscriptAnalyzer`:\\n       - `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition(sessionRef)` - **READS** transcript file\\n       - Parses transcript to find position\\n\\n3. **Ensure strategy setup:**\\n   - `strat.EnsureSetup()` - Strategy-specific initialization (may create branches)\\n\\n4. **Initialize session:**\\n   - `strat.InitializeSession()` - Creates/updates session state\\n\\n5. **Log output:**\\n   - Writes to stderr\\n   - Writes to `.entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n**Key I/O Summary:**\\n- Reads: `.git/`, working tree status, transcript file\\n- Writes: `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-*.json`, git branches/objects, `.git/entire-sessions/`, `.entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. STOP HOOK (Turn End)\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 169-179) - ParseHookEvent\\n- `lifecycle.go` (lines 150-424) - handleLifecycleTurnEnd (COMPLEX: 8 major steps)\\n\\n**Event Flow:**\\n```\\nParseHookEvent → parseTurnEnd()\\n  ↓\\nDispatchLifecycleEvent → handleLifecycleTurnEnd()\\n```\\n\\n**I/O Operations (this is the most I/O-heavy hook):**\\n\\n1. **Parse input from stdin:**\\n   - Reads JSON from stdin\\n\\n2. **Early checks:**\\n   - `fileExists(transcriptRef)` - **READS** transcript file to verify it exists\\n   - `strategy.OpenRepository()` - Opens `.git/`\\n   - `IsEmptyRepository()` - Checks if repo has commits\\n\\n3