tatus\\n      - Filters out pre-existing untracked files\\n\\n13. **Filter and normalize paths:**\\n    - `FilterAndNormalizePaths()` - Path transformations (no I/O)\\n\\n14. **Filter to uncommitted files:**\\n    - `openRepository()` - Opens `.git/`\\n    - `repo.Head()` - **READS** HEAD reference\\n    - `repo.CommitObject()` - **READS** HEAD commit object\\n    - `commit.Tree()` - **READS** HEAD tree\\n    - `headTree.File()` - **READS** files from HEAD tree\\n    - `os.ReadFile()` - **READS** working tree files (for content comparison)\\n\\n15. **Check if there are changes:**\\n    - If no changes: **READS/WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json` for state transition\\n\\n16. **Create context file:**\\n    - `os.WriteFile()` - **WRITES** `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/context.md`\\n\\n17. **Get git author:**\\n    - `GetGitAuthor()` - **READS**:\\n      - `.git/config` (via go-git)\\n      - Falls back to `git config user.name` and `git config user.email` commands\\n\\n18. **Get strategy and calculate token usage:**\\n    - Strategy-specific operations\\n    - May read subagent transcript files\\n\\n19. **Save step checkpoint:**\\n    - `strat.SaveStep(ctx)` - Strategy-specific:\\n      - **CREATES/WRITES** git objects\\n      - **CREATES/WRITES** metadata on branches\\n      - **WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json`\\n\\n20. **Update transcript position (auto-commit only):**\\n    - **READS/WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json`\\n\\n21. **Transition session phase:**\\n    - `TransitionAndLog()` + `SaveSessionState()` - **READS/WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json`\\n\\n22. **Cleanup pre-prompt state:**\\n    - `os.Remove()` - **DELETES** `.entire/tmp/pre-prompt-*.json`\\n\\n23. **Log output:**\\n    - Multiple `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, ...)` calls\\n    - Writes to `.entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n**Total I/O for STOP Hook: ~30 distinct operations**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. SESSION-END HOOK\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 182-192) - ParseHookEvent\\n- `lifecycle.go` (lines 460-475) - handleLifecycleSessionEnd\\n\\n**I/O Operations:**\\n\\n1. **Parse input from stdin**\\n\\n2. **Mark session ended:**\\n   - `LoadSessionState()` - **READS** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json`\\n   - `TransitionAndLog()` - State machine transition\\n   - `SaveSessionState()` - **WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json`\\n\\n3. **Set EndedAt timestamp:**\\n   - `os.WriteFile()` - **WRITES** `.git/entire-sessions/<sessionid>.json` with EndedAt field\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. PRE-TASK HOOK\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 195-207) - ParseHookEvent\\n- `lifecycle.go` (lines 478-498) - handleLifecycleSubagentStart\\n\\n**I/O Operations:**\\n\\n1. **Parse input from stdin:**\\n   - Reads JSON from stdin\\n\\n2. **Capture pre-task state:**\\n   - `CapturePreTaskState()` (from `state.go`, lines 392-433):\\n     - `paths.AbsPath()` - Uses repo root\\n     - **CREATES** `.entire/tmp/` directory\\n     - `getUntrackedFilesForState()` - **READS** working tree status\\n     - **WRITES** `.entire/tmp/pre-task-<tooluseid>.json`\\n\\n3. **Log output:**\\n   - Writes to stderr\\n   - Writes to `.entire/logs/entire.log`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. POST-TASK HOOK\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` (lines 210-227) - ParseHookEvent\\n- `lifecycle.go` (lines 501-623) - handleLifecycleSubagentEnd\\n\\n**I/O Operations:**\\n\\n1. **Parse input from stdin:**\\n   - Reads JSON from stdin (session_id, transcript_path, tool_use_id, etc.)\\n\\n2. **Parse subagent type from tool input:**\\n   - `ParseSubagentTypeAndDescription()` - Parses JSON (no I/O)\\n\\n3. **Determine subagent transcript path:**\\n   - `fileExists()` - **READS** subagent transcript path (if exists)\\n\\n4. **Extract modified files from subagent transcript:**\\n   - If `TranscriptAnalyzer`:\\n     - **READS** subagent transcript file\\n     - Parses JSONL for file modifications\\n\\n5. **Load pre-tas