sions/` | ~2 ops |\\n| **pre-task** | Lifecycle | `.git/`, working tree | `.entire/tmp/` | ~3 ops |\\n| **post-task** | Lifecycle | `.git/`, transcript, session state, `.git/config` | git objects, metadata | ~8 ops |\\n| **post-todo** | Claude-specific | `.entire/tmp/`, `.git/`, session state, settings | git objects, metadata, `.entire/logs/` | ~7 ops |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Startup Latency Sources (Ordered by Impact)\\n\\n### CRITICAL PATH (Before Claude Code sees \\\"Ready\\\"):\\n\\n1. **Session-Start Hook** (~50-150ms):\\n   - Settings load (2 files)\\n   - Session state directory scan\\n   - Logging initialization + directory creation\\n   - Output banner message\\n\\n2. **User-Prompt-Submit Hook** (~100-500ms):\\n   - Untracked file scan (full `git status`)\\n   - Transcript position detection (parses existing transcript)\\n   - Session initialization\\n   - Create `.entire/tmp/` directory\\n\\n3. **All Subsequent Hooks** (on Turn End, ~1-10s):\\n   - **STOP hook is the bottleneck:**\\n     - Full transcript read + JSON parsing (100KB-10MB+)\\n     - Prompt extraction from all messages\\n     - Summary extraction from last message\\n     - Modified files detection (full git status + HEAD tree traversal)\\n     - Commit object creation\\n\\n### NOT on Critical Path (Fire asynchronously):\\n\\n- **Session-End** - Fires after user closes session\\n- **Pre-Task/Post-Task** - Fire during subagent execution\\n- **Post-Todo** - Incremental, only if in subagent and files changed\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File System Impact Summary\\n\\n### Reads (No caching, happens every hook):\\n- `.entire/settings.json` (small, ~1KB)\\n- `.entire/settings.local.json` (if exists, small)\\n- `.git/` directory (go-git library handles)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/` (all session state files)\\n- Working tree status (git status operation)\\n- `.entire/logs/entire.log` (append)\\n\\n### Writes (Always):\\n- `.entire/logs/entire.log` (buffered, 8KB buffer)\\n- `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` (on 