es (like a monorepo root) is expensive to parse\\n- **Many commits on the ref path** — walking commit parents\\n- **Large pack index in memory** — go-git loads the full `.idx` file\\n\\nTo simulate a genuinely large repo, we'd need to create 10k+ *tracked files committed to a tree*, not just orphaned blobs. Our `RepoFiles` dimension from the earlier benchmark did this, but only went to 1000 files — and session-start doesn't walk the tree anyway.\\n\\nThe real question is whether `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` (called 7-8 times as a subprocess) is slow on the customer's repo. That's a `git` CLI cost, not a go-git cost, and our benchmark doesn't distinguish between them because our `.git/` is always on a fast local SSD in a small temp dir.\\n\\nWant me to add a dimension that measures pure `git rev-parse` subprocess cost in isolation, so we can see what fraction of the 80ms floor comes from those spawns?\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":150846,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":150846},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYRdZK6w19hbcLDQdqTy2\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"fc7a8d39-0bd8-484b-a1ff-bc290ec2653d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T20:28:07.554Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fc7a8d39-0bd8-484b-a1ff-bc290ec2653d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"960fa682-812c-41ee-859c-1136484fe07f\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"optimize_claude_start\",\"slug\":\"ancient-mixing-hearth\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"8cff19b4-9ad8-4f09-9b07-d24c581b936c\",\"toolUseID\":\"8cff19b4-9ad